Joao Felix has suggested he may stay at Chelsea beyond the summer as he enjoys the ‘freedom’ offered to him at Stamford Bridge. Joao Felix joined Chelsea on loan from Atletico Madrid in January and has had a mixed start to his time at the club. He was given his marching orders on his Blues’ debut against Fulham and missed three games with the resulting ban. Confed Cup: Rivers Utd fired up ahead of Motema Pembe clash D’Tigers overcome Guinea to keep World Cup quest alive However, since he returned, he has looked like an inspired piece of business. He scored his first goal for the club against West Ham earlier this month and has regularly been Chelsea’s most exciting player in games.